tates founded in  by rocco b commisso it serves primarily smaller markets in the midwest and southern united states formerly a publicly traded firm it went private in a  million transaction in march  and is as of  owned by commisso contents  coverage  sports  reputation  carriage disputes involving mediacom  june  carriage dispute with granite broadcasting  july  carriage dispute with media general  mediacom views on carriage disputes and retransmission blackouts  references  external links coverageedit mediacom offers service in  states about  of mediacoms subscription base is in the th through th ranked television markets it is the largest cable company in iowa and second largest in illinois examples of cities with mediacom service include albany columbus tifton and valdosta in georgia iowa city cedar rapids and des moines in iowa columbia jefferson city and springfield in missouri and the quad cities on the iowaillinois border mediacom also serves outlying areas on the florida gulf coast and around minneapolis minnesota in reporting its results for the fourth quarter and full year  mediacom describes itself as the th largest us cable company with  customer relationships at the end of   in february  multichannel news reported that mediacom was the th largest multichannel video programming distributor in the us with  video customers of  homes passed places where mediacom service can be ordered  of have subscribed to basic cable with mediacom and  have subscribed to mediacom internet service of homes with basic cable  also have digital cable service counting basic cable digital cable highspeed data and cable telephony as separate revenue mediacom had  revenue generating units rgus at the end of   of customers had at least two of video internet and phone from mediacom and  had all three over the previous five years video decreased from  of mediacoms revenue to  at the end of  mediacom announced it would become the first major us cable company to fully transition to the docsis  platform a new generation of broadband technology in january  mediacom launched  gbps internet service across its entire iowa footprint and as a result all of the nearly  million households in the more than  iowa communities passed by mediacom’s iowa network now have access to download speeds that are up to  times faster than the minimum broadband definition set by the fcc according to mediacom’s website  gbps internet service is also available in portions of alabama and missouri and by the end of  will be made available to every single community where mediacom offers internet service sportsedit mediacom broadcasts local sports programming on its connections channel mc along with a simulcast of espnews other sports channels on the mediacom lineup as of september  include nfl network big ten network sec network and the national feed of the yes network mediacom does not carry nhl network mlb network or nba tv or tennis channel reputationedit in  mediacom communications was named the nations top communications provider by the leading industry publication cablefax  in a  telecom report conducted by acsi mediacom occupied last place in customer satisfaction among all companies in the acsi regardless of industry in a survey conducted by consumer reports magazine in  mediacom is the worst cable provider in the country according to the  people polled the september   edition of pc magazine named mediacom one of the nation’s worst  fastest internet service providers the des moines business record in its  best of des moines issue gave mediacom the top award for best local internet service provider and best company use of social media as reported in the chicago tribune july   in july  mediacom was named by the fcc as one of the nation’s top  internet service providers when it comes to delivering advertised speeds to consumers the february  issue of consumer reports ranked mediacom amongst the worst cable companies in the united states th of  in tv service th of  in internet service and last of  in phone service based on surveys the deepening of this trend was affirmed in the june  issue of consumer reports in which mediacom was identified as the worstrated company in the united states regarding tv service phone service and bundled telecom services and the third worst isp only above the two satellite internet companies wild blue and hughes net carriage disputes involving mediacomedit june  carriage dispute with granite broadcastingedit on june   mediacom subscribers in three television markets served by granite broadcasting corporation stations were unable to view those stations over mediacom cable due to a carriage dispute between mediacom and granite broadcasting over retransmission consent fees the affected granite broadcasting stations included weektv in peoria illinois kbjrtv in superior wisconsinduluth minnesota and wisetv in fort wayne indiana all three of which are primary nbc affiliates on june   mediacom and granite broadcasting reached an agreement thereby restoring granite stations to mediacom cable systems the agreement came just in time for game  of the  stanley cup finals which was broadcast on nbc two days later july  carriage dispute with media generaledit on july   media general pulled its stations off of mediacom cable systems across the united states due to a carriage dispute over retransmission consent fees this carriage dispute saw media general stations disappear from mediacom lineups in  television markets across the united states and even three of the fox affiliates owned by media general were lost to mediacom subscribers in hampton roads virginia terre haute indiana and topeka kansas just before the start of the  major league baseball allstar game on july   mediacom and media general reached a new agreement thereby restoring media general owned stations to mediacom subscribers in the affected areas mediacom views on carriage disputes and retransmission blackoutsedit on july   mediacom filed a petition with the federal communications commission to limit or prevent blackouts of local broadcast stations during carriage disputes according to mediacom ceo rocco commisso the fcc has frequently neglected to address concerns regarding retransmission consent and blackouts of local television stations particularly in rural areas where residents have a more difficult time receiving an acceptable overtheair signal commissos proposal was for local broadcasters not to terminate a cable or satellite providers carriage of the stations signal at the end of a retransmission consent agreement if the station does not reach a minimum of  percent of its local viewers within its dma either overtheair or via its online stream commisso also made note of the fact that retransmission consent fees double every two or three years something which never happens in any other industry referencesedit  a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p mediacom communications corporation  annual report to shareholders ars and form k for the fiscal year ended december   securities and exchange commission retrieved    mediacom communications and seth miller complete goingprivate transaction middletown new york businesswireberkshire hathaway  retrieved    mediacom cable overview and coverage broadbandnowcom retrieved    httpirmediacomcablecomphoenixzhtmlcpirolnewsarticleid  httpwwwmultichannelcomtopmvpds  httpwwwlightreadingcomcabledocsismediacomgoingalldocsisbyyearendddid  httpswwwcedmagazinecomnewsmediacomrollsgigacrossiowa  httpsmediacomcablecomproductsinternetgig  httpwwwbusinesswirecomnewshomeenmediacomcommunicationsnamednationestopcableoperator  httpwwwtheacsiorgnewsandresourcespressreleasespresspressreleasetelecommunications  httpwwwpresscitizencomarticlenewsconsumerreportssurveymediacomistheworstodysseytabctopnewsctextcfrontpagenclickcheck  pc magazine the fastest isps in the us   business record best of des moines  fcc reports mediacom consistently delivers advertised internet speeds  smith will  magazine pans 